SR 30 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 30 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 30(By Senators Queen, Morris, and Jeffries)[Introduced March 13, 2025] Recognizing the 80th anniversary of the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation.Whereas, In 1944 the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation was established by Michael Late Benedum, born and raised in Bridgeport, WV, and his wife, Sarah Lantz Benedum born and raised in Blacksville, WV; and Whereas, The Foundation was named for the couple’s son, Claude Worthington Benedum, who died at the age of 20 from the 1918 flu epidemic while working for the United States Army; and Whereas, The Foundation is the largest philanthropic foundation contributing primarily to West Virginia organizations and was established for the express purpose of grantmaking for worthy causes and events focused on West Virginia and Pittsburgh, the native and adopted homes of Mr. & Mrs. Benedum; and  Whereas, Through its leadership and staff, the Foundation has successfully carried out this mission for 80 years; and  Whereas, The Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation has focused its efforts on the three noteworthy program areas to include Community & Economic Development, Education, and Health; and  Whereas, Since 2001, the Foundation has expanded its mission to include funding for Entrepreneurship as a Strategic Initiative; and Whereas, The Foundation has invested millions of dollars in funding in West Virginia for rural economic development and entrepreneurship; and  Whereas, The Foundation was instrumental in the establishment and advancement of the West Virginia Entrepreneurship Ecosystem through substantial investment and professional support; and  Whereas, The Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation continues to play a critical leadership role in the development of entrepreneurship and economic development throughout West Virginia; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the West Virginia State Senate recognizes the tremendous impact that the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation has had throughout West Virginia with the sincere hope that the Foundation continues its mission and good works throughout West Virginia; and, be it Further Resolved, That the mission of the Foundation has been instrumental in community and economic development since its inception in 1944, by the late Michael and Sarah Benedum; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the appropriate representative of the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


